HEADWORD: Rhaetic
<hw>Rhae"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Rhaeticus</ets> Rhetian.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Pertining
to, or of the same horizon as, certain Mesozoic strata of the Rhetian
Alps. These strata are regarded as closing the Triassic period. See the
<xex>Chart</xex> of <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhaetizite</ent>⟦br⟧
